  <brief_title>Chinese Adolescent Registry for Diabetes (CARD) Study</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Qilu Hospital of Shandong University</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Qilu Hospital of Shandong University</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The CARD study is a observational study which includes Chinese adolescents with diabetes aged
      18-30. The study aims to explore the status of disease treatment, self-management, the
      relationship between disease treatment and disease outcome in Chinese adolescents with
      diabetes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
